DIGEST
SCR 24 Original 2026 Regular Session Womack
Changes the rule governing CWD Control Areas. Defines "apparent prevalence" as the
percentage of confirmed CWD detections within a surveillance season. Changes the term for
the geographic area contemplated by the rule from "Control Area" to "CWD management
zone".
Defines "CWD management zone" as the area established for surveillance and mitigation
in response to the detection of CWD. Creates a five-mile zone and a 15-mile zone around
the location of a confirmed CWD deer.
Defines "supplemental feed/bait" as substances used to attract wild quadrapeds or birds.
Defines "surveillance goal" as the probability of detecting CWD at 1.5% prevalence with
95% confidence, from a minimum of 300 samples.
Defines "surveillance season" as the period of sample collection, July one-June 30.
Provides for establishment of a management zone upon detection of CWD outside of the
existing management zone. Provides for modification of the management zone only if CWD
is detected outside the five-mile zone. Requires changes to management zone be via
emergency declaration by the secretary, subject to ratification or amendment by the
commission at its next meeting, and publication of the map on LDWF's website.
Requires LDWF to use easily identifiable zone boundaries, to establish five-mile and 15-
mile zones as closely as practicable to each zone's actual radius, and allows LDWF to
consider inclusion of processors, taxidermists, WMA's, and refuges in establishing
management zones.
