Requires removal of the CWD management zone when surveillance goals are met for three
consecutive surveillance seasons.
For carcass export restrictions, changes the term for the geographic area from "CWD Control
Area" to "CWD management zone".
Allows baiting and supplemental feeding with the 5-mile zone and 15-mile zone September
first-March 31, only when prevalence is below 1.5% and annual surveillance goals are met,
subject to commission approval or modification.
Requires hunters to check for bait prior to each hunt.
Provides that bait and feed restrictions for a new or modified management zone are effective
upon the later of season closure or 30 days after confirmation of a CWD index case, subject
to commission approval or modification.
Allows use of bait not normally eaten by deer for feral hog trapping or by permitted bear
hunters during the designated bear baiting season.
Provides that properties of 40 or more acres within the 5-mile zone are eligible for Tier 1
DMAP liberalized bag limit and season length at no cost, if the entire property is within the
specified zone. Allows for issuance of replacement tags to the harvester of a CWD-positive
deer.
Directs transmission of copies of the resolution to the department and the commission.
Directs the La. Register to print the amendments in the La. Administrative Code.
